.TH "smack_audit_rule_init" 9 "smack_audit_rule_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
smack_audit_rule_init \- Initialize a smack audit rule
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" smack_audit_rule_init
.BI "(u32 field "  ","
.BI "u32 op "  ","
.BI "char *rulestr "  ","
.BI "void **vrule "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "field" 12
audit rule fields given from user-space (audit.h)
.IP "op" 12
required testing operator (=, !=, >, <, ...)
.IP "rulestr" 12
smack label to be audited
.IP "vrule" 12
pointer to save our own audit rule representation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Prepare to audit cases where (\fIfield\fP \fIop\fP \fIrulestr\fP) is true.
The label to be audited is created if necessay.
